This is almost not worth explaining because no one should ever do this.
There were a lot of technical and design-dependent reasons we had to do it this way (or at least, reasons that this was one viable solution).
Basically we turned a parameter timeline into a step sequencer. Every X frames, the game increments parameter "sixteenth_note" up 1, and over time we get music.
That's probably all you really need to know.
